{"questionId":"9076543","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A beam of coherent monochromatic light from a distant galaxy is used in an optics experiment on Earth.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The beam is incident normally on a double slit. The distance between the slits is 0.300 mm. A screen is at a distance <em>D </em>from the slits. The diffraction angle <em>θ </em>is labelled.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4685/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-10_om_17.53.34.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP2/ENG/TZ1/03.a\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>The wavelength of the beam as observed on Earth is 633.0 nm. The separation between a dark and a bright fringe on the screen is 4.50 mm. Calculate <em>D</em>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>evidence of solving for <em>D&nbsp;</em>«<em>D</em> <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\frac{{sd}}{\\lambda }\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>s</mi>\n      <mi>d</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>λ</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>» ✔</p>\n<p>«<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{4.50 \\times {{10}^{ - 3}} \\times 0.300 \\times {{10}^{ - 3}}}}{{633.0 \\times {{10}^{ - 9}}}} \\times 2\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4.50</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.300</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>633.0</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>9</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>» = 4.27 «m»&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[1]</strong> max for 2.13 m.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076543","referenceCode":"18M.2.HL.TZ1.3a.iii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The wavelength of the beam as observed on Earth is 633.0 nm. The separation between a dark and a bright fringe on the screen is 4.50 mm. Calculate D.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 4: Waves","4.2 – Travelling waves","Core","Topic 4: Waves"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}